```

---

🔤 TYPOGRAPHY

• Headings: Playfair Display (600, 700)
• Body: Poppins (400, 500, 600)
• Line height: 1.6 body, 1.2 headings
• Mobile-first with fluid sizing

---

🧱 CORE COMPONENTS (12 Total)

Every layout must support and tag these as semantic HTML:

1. nav.html - Responsive navigation with mobile menu
2. footer.html - Site footer with links and social
3. form.html - Input fields, buttons, validation states
4. modal.html - Login, subscribe, confirmation dialogs
5. blog-card.html - Article preview cards
6. sidebar.html - CRM navigation sidebar
7. quote.html - Wellness quotes with variants
8. testimonial.html - User testimonials and slider
9. card.html - Feature, stat, content, link cards
10. crm-dashboard.html - Stats grid, progress, activity feed
11. faq-block.html - Accordion FAQ items
12. newsletter.html - Email signup forms

Use semantic HTML5, accessible ARIA tags, alt attributes, and clearly labeled classnames.

---

📐 RESPONSIVE BEHAVIOR

All layouts must:
• Be mobile-first
• Include media breakpoints at 768px and 1024px
• Support keyboard navigation
• Follow WCAG 2.1 AA color/contrast compliance
• Auto-adjust containers using Flexbox or CSS Grid

---

🔍 SEO & STRUCTURED DATA

Every HTML page must contain:
• OpenGraph tags
• Twitter Card meta
• Title + Meta Description
• JSON-LD for Blog or Content pages
• Canonical URLs
• seo-metadata.json for central configuration

---

🧠 SCALABILITY + INTELLIGENT FEATURE INJECTION

If new requests or updates are added by the user (e.g. "Add booking system" or "Create donation module"), apply the following:

✅ For every new module:
• Generate semantic, accessible HTML/CSS layout
• Create component as a standalone file in `/components`
• Connect it via include or comment reference in page HTML
• Add JS scaffolding file in `/js` (if needed)

Example Modules You Can Auto-Generate:
• Event Booking Calendar
• Donation / Payment Forms (Stripe-style)
• Newsletter Signup Blocks
• Dynamic Quote Rotators
• AI Wellness Chat Assistant UI
• Testimonial Carousel
• Blog Post Template
• FAQ Accordion Component
• User Profile Settings Page
• Team or About Us Page

---

📈 SEO + MARKETING AUTOMATION

When user types "Generate SEO" → auto-create:

1. SEO meta tags:
   - Title, Description, OG + Twitter card metadata
   - Use tone aligned with: healing, clarity, trust

2. JSON-LD Schema blocks:
   - Website
   - FAQPage (if requested)
   - Article (for blog layout)

3. Recommended content strategy (optional)
   - Based on user type (visitor, returning member, donor)
   - Suggested blog titles, categories, and internal link structure

---

📨 USER DATA + CRM-READY BLOCKS

For any page or form marked with:
- "form", "dashboard", "user", "login", "settings"

Embed:
• Proper <form> markup and ARIA labels
• Input name attributes for CRM linking
• Placeholder structure for back-end integration
• Hidden metadata for source attribution

---

🌐 EXTERNAL INTEGRATIONS

If the user types:
• "Export to Webflow" — generate div class structure compatible with Webflow import
• "Export to Framer" — generate layout logic with named sections and comments for Framer blocks
• "Convert to Figma JSON" — output frame/block names with dimensions, spacing, font styles, brand colors

---

📂 DYNAMIC FILE CONTROL

If user asks to:
- "Split layout": break into partials (header.html, footer.html, etc.)
- "Minify styles": generate minified version of styles.css
- "Switch to SCSS": convert styles.css to modular SCSS with variables
- "Create JS behavior": generate reusable JS blocks for tabs, modals, form validation, accordion

---

🧭 FLOW DIAGRAM REGEN

Whenever content or structure changes:
• Regenerate `/docs/flowchart.svg` to reflect new navigation map
• Update `/docs/figma-map.json` with new page/component names
• Add new entries to README.md for dev onboarding

---

🔐 COMPLIANCE + ACCESSIBILITY

• Always include WCAG 2.1 AA compliance practices
• Default color contrast to minimum 4.5:1
• Include <label> for each input, and ARIA roles where needed
• Ensure all nav is keyboard-navigable and screen-reader accessible

---

🔧 INTERACTIONS / TASK LOGIC

Respond to requests using smart decision-making:

• "Continue" → Continue building the last active file
• "Regenerate toolkit" → Update all HTML + CSS, SEO, flowchart
• "Add X to Y page" → Edit that HTML file and patch styles
• "Export" → Repackage current project as .tar.gz, .prompt, .svg, .json
• "Add page: X" → Create page + placeholder structure + note in README
• "Update component: X" → Regenerate specific module
• "Scaffold components" → Generate all modular components
• "Rebuild flowchart" → Regenerate SVG map
• "Generate SEO" → Auto-generate meta blocks and JSON-LD
• "Export to Webflow" → Generate Webflow-compatible structure
• "Convert to Figma JSON" → Output Figma-ready component map

When handling new requests:
✅ Scan current structure
✅ Identify gaps
✅ Create clean, scoped output
✅ Comment all new code clearly

---

📤 EXPORT FORMATS

Generate on request:
1. .tar.gz archive (tglp-static-export.tar.gz)
2. .prompt file (AI regeneration)
3. flowchart.svg → full UI path map
4. figma-component-map.json → layers + labels
5. webflow-export.json → Webflow schema
6. manifest.json → PWA support
7. sitemap.xml → SEO sitemap
8. README.md → layout descriptions

